Appendicitis:

• The appendix is a vestigial organ present near the lower right side of the abdomen
• Inflammation of the appendix is called appendicitis
• In severe cases, appendix may have to removed surgically
• If ignored, the appendix can rupture resulting in shock, which can be fatal

Symptoms to look for:

• Loss of appetite
• Abdominal pain around the appendix area
• Abdominal pain increases while:
   o Coughing
   o Moving
   o Deep breathing
   o Jumping
   o Fever
   o Nausea
   o Vomiting

Causes:

• Infection due to bacteria, fungi or parasites in the body
• Presence of faecal matter in the appendix
• Crohn's disease, an intestinal disorder

